---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
---
<Layout>
<main class="w-full max-w-5xl">
    <div class="mt-16">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 justify-between items-center">
            <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-6xl text-indigo-400">Writing</h2>
            <span
                class="text-xl sm:text-2xl px-2 sm:px-3 py-1 sm:py-2 rounded-full border border-slate-500/20"
                >22nd March 2024</span
            >
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-6xl text-pretty sm:text-8xl text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-200 mt-8">
            Layouts in Astro
        </h1>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">Summary</h2>
        <p
            class="text-xl text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 mt-2 max-w-prose"
        >
            Understanding how to use layout efficiently in Astro, helps you with better structuring of your codebase allowing you to leverage same structure, optimising for SEO and producing a more maintainable website along with you can use it as entry point for loading third party script, accross your website!
        </p>
    </div>
    </main>
</Layout>